# .gitignore for prawl.fft.itemoverhaul
#
# Self-contained: this repo does NOT rely on ~/.gitignore_global. Every rule the
# project needs lives here so a fresh clone on any machine ignores the right
# things (the global was silently swallowing *.sqlite, __pycache__, etc.).

# --- Python (tools/ + working/ scripts) ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# --- .NET build artifacts (LivingWeapon mod) ---
bin/
obj/
*.pdb

# --- SQLite caches (decode/reference DBs; never source) ---
# This is why a stray ability.sqlite stub used to vanish from `git status`.
*.sqlite

# --- Load-bearing build inputs that are NOT committed ---
# working/ = sqlite/icon caches + decoded refs (patch_names.py, recolor_icons.py,
#            decode_tables.py, generate.py read from here). out/ = generate.py handoff.
working/
out/

# --- Release / packaging artifacts ---
Publish/
dist/
*.zip

# --- OS / editor cruft ---
*.tmp
*.temp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vs/
.vscode/
*.user

# NOTE: mod/FFTIVC/ (generated tables + nxd + icons) IS committed for now — the
# item.en.nxd build is still a manual step, so we preserve the working artifacts.

# A case-insensitive "Icon" rule (from some global/OS ignore files, e.g. the
# macOS Icon\r marker) ignores our whole ui/ffto/icon/ tree on a case-insensitive
# filesystem. Re-include the equip icons so they stay tracked regardless:
!mod/FFTIVC/data/enhanced/ui/ffto/icon/
!mod/FFTIVC/data/enhanced/ui/ffto/icon/**

# Local-only: third-party Move-Find FAQ (copyright; referenced by docs/treasure_master_prototype.md)
treasure.txt

# Local-only: rolling session handoff doc (rewritten each session; not part of the repo)
docs/HANDOFF.md
